{
  "texts": [
    "The action recognition model should be based on the real long-tail action distribution (Horn and Perona 2017) rather than on an artificially balanced dataset.",
    "(6) MEVA (Corona et al. 2021) Datasets used for action recognition often fail to meet public safety community requirements, for example AVA, moments in time (Monfort et al. 2019), and YouTube-8 M (Abu-El-Haija et al. 2016).",
    "These datasets present short, high-resolution video specificities centered on the activity of interest in both time and space.",
    "In real life, more datasets are required with an actual spatial scope.",
    "Multiview extended video with activities (MEVA) is a new dataset for human action recognition."
  ]
}